How much money does it take per year to live <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>comfortably</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the U.S.?<br>
<br>
Throw out some more numbers.  Again, we'll agree on it.<br>
<br>
How much does the average artist/musician/record label exec make a year?<br>
<br>
Can everyone agree that they're making a hell of a lot more than either of the numbers agreed upon in the first 2 questions?<br>
<br>
They're only bitching because they're wasteful.  If an artist makes a million dollars and sticks it in an overseas bank where it cannot be taxed by our government, more likely than not they could live off the interest alone.<br>
<br>
Is it their fault for losing money?  No.<br>
<br>
Is it their fault for not saving the money they make to get by in &quot;hard times&quot; such as these?  Hell yes.<br>
<br>
Munky, the bassist from KORN, collects mercedes or beemers, can't remember which.  Does someone really need THAT MUCH money?  I can understand certain fulfillments, but grow up.  If they were making just enough to get by, and started losing money, they could complain.  They're not.<br>
<br>
Stop crying over spilled milk and grow the fuck up.<br>
<br>
Want an analogy that pertains to this?  Robin Hood.<br>
<br>
Napster/Kazaa/Morpheus/Any P2P program is the Robin Hood of this day and age's music industry producer/consumer relationship.<br>
<br>
Yes, it's stealing.  Yes, two wrongs don't make a right.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, who the fuck cares?  They haven't found a solution, and it's not going to work.  AND in the years it will take to sue as many people as they do, how many other lookalikes will pop up?  Do they have the time and energy to continue suing people for the rest of human civilization?<br>
<br>
And while I'm on the whole &quot;two wrongs don't make a right&quot; thing, we went in, bombed a country and killed innocent people to take a madman out of power.  Now we're still there, and some people are starting to think they'd rather have the madman back.  Two wrongs sure seemed to have made a right in that situation to a lot of people on these boards...<br>
<br>
AND, do point out the counterproductivity of arguing that fining/suing them is ok, I have yet to see a law that says that downloading music is illegal.  Therefore suing/fing someone who didn't really break a law (written...if you start arguing morality you'll just dig yourself deeper) would be another wrong in it's own right, would it not?<br>
<br>
Aerdor Dewcatcher<br>
53rd druid<br>
